+#### BLOCKER — `tests/test_intraday.py:285` — IndentationError breaks entire test suite
+
+**File**: `tests/test_intraday.py`, line 285  
+**Issue**: The line `self.assertEqual(mock_is_live.call_count, 2)` is indented to 4 spaces (class-body level) while the preceding line 284 and following lines 286–287 are all at 8 spaces (method level). Python raises `IndentationError: unindent does not match any outer indentation level` at compile time — the module cannot be imported at all.
+
+```python
+# Lines 284–287 as read from disk:
+        self.assertEqual(mock_fetch.call_count, 2)   # 8 spaces ✓
+    self.assertEqual(mock_is_live.call_count, 2)      # 4 spaces ✗ — class level
+        self.assertEqual(len(first), 1)               # 8 spaces ✓
+        self.assertEqual(len(second), 2)              # 8 spaces ✓
