+**Issue:** `_align_session` for `"regular"` and `"crypto"` are tested, including two DST cases. The `"extended"` branch (04:00–20:00 ET, Mon–Fri) has no test. The `weekday_mask` applied there is identical in structure to the regular branch but has never been exercised.  
+**Impact:** A regression silently including Saturday/Sunday bars or misaligning the 04:00/20:00 ET boundaries would go undetected.  
+**Minimal fix:** Add one test with a mix of: a pre-04:00 ET bar, an in-range bar, a post-20:00 ET bar, and a Saturday bar. Assert only the in-range weekday bar survives.
+
+---
+
+#### LOW — L1: Exception type inconsistency for unsupported vendor
+
+**Files:** `tradingagents/dataflows/intraday.py:289`, `tradingagents/dataflows/interface.py:202`  
+**Issue:** `fetch_intraday_bars` raises `NotImplementedError` for an unknown vendor; `interface.get_intraday_bars` raises `ValueError` for the same condition.  
+**Impact:** Callers catching one type get unexpected propagation from the other entry point.  
+**Minimal fix:** Document that `NotImplementedError` is the canonical signal for stub vendors, and align interface.py to raise `NotImplementedError` as well (single-line change).
+
+---
+
+#### LOW — L2: Cache key entropy inconsistency
+
+**Files:** `tradingagents/dataflows/intraday.py:71` (20 hex chars, 80 bits), `tradingagents/graph/prefilter.py:31` (`_get_cache_path`, 16 hex chars, 64 bits)  
+**Issue:** Two SHA-256 cache-key implementations with different truncation lengths.  
+**Impact:** No practical collision risk at either length for realistic workloads. Purely cosmetic inconsistency.  
+**Minimal fix:** Standardize on 20 chars in a single-line edit to `prefilter.py:31`.
